vukašin (cyrillic script: вукашин) is an old slavic name of serbian origin. it is composed from two words: vuk (wolf) and sin (son), so it means sin vuka (son of wolf). in some places in croatia and bosnia it can be found as a surname. the name vukašin can be found in serbia, macedonia, montenegro, bulgaria, republika srpska and croatia (used by serbs of croatia). during sound change phoneme s became š.